<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,397,1394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1189,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[322,547,1189,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sphaerion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iuasanga" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,547,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">Sphaerion iuasanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[553,643,1189,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[553,643,1189,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Gahan,1903" authorityName="Gahan" authorityYear="1903" box="[769,1020,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sphaerion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sladeni">
<emphasis box="[769,877,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">S. sladeni</emphasis>
Gahan, 
<number box="[965,1020,1189,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" value="1903.0">1903</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Burmeister, 1865" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1865" box="[1075,1401,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sphaerion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusticum">
<emphasis box="[1075,1089,1190,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1103,1201,1190,1213]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">rusticum</emphasis>
Burmeister, 
<number box="[1345,1401,1189,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" value="1865.0">1865</number>
</taxonomicName>
by the reddish-brown to dark-brown integument. It differs from them by the reddish-orange head, scape, and legs contrasting with the rest of the integument; center of pronotum glabrous, shining from base to apex, wider at posterior third. In 
<taxonomicName box="[353,461,1297,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sphaerion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sladeni">
<emphasis box="[353,461,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">S. sladeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[514,639,1298,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sphaerion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rusticum">
<emphasis box="[514,639,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="441">S. rusticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the scape and legs are similar in color to the rest of the integument and the center of pronotum has a short, narrow shining area. It can be included in the alternative of couplet 
<number box="[1295,1311,1334,1358]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" value="3.0">3</number>
, with these two species, in 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[324,492,1369,1394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" refString="Martins, U. R. (2005) Tribo Elaphidionini. In: Martins, U. R. (Org.), Cerambycidae Sul-americanos (Coleoptera). Taxonomia. Vol. 7. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 1 - 393." type="book" year="2005">
Martins (
<number box="[426,485,1369,1394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="441" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
key.
</paragraph>
